<h2 id="section-top">Ophthalmology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=27">Barking, Havering and Redbridge University Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent3ba6b675233b4569afb1483f7a6523c2">
</div>
<p>We are based in Team 2 (first floor) of Queen's Hospital and have one of the largest ophthalmology departments in the country.<br/><br/>We have a dedicated eye casualty department that takes walk-ins and referals from GPs. We also provide outpatient care and day surgery.<br/><br/>Our specialist teams of consultants diagnose and treat a wide range of eye conditions in adults, young people and children supported by ophthalmic nurses and technicians and orthoptists.<br/><br/>We have outreach clinics at Loxford and Brentwood and many of our consultants work closely with the community offering medical and professional support where needed.</p>
<p>We offer treatment for cataracts, glaucoma, diabetic retinopathy, age-related macular degeneration (AMD), detached retinas, squints, corneal infections, conjunctivitis and eye injuries.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
